id: pm-jek2
title: "GH-262: prevent path-like pm init from corrupting caller tracker settings"
description: GitHub issue #262 reports pm init /tmp/target being parsed as an id prefix and rewriting the current project settings. Fix path-like positional disambiguation and require --force before init rewrites existing tracker settings.
type: Issue
status: closed
priority: 1
tags[3]: agent-ux,github-262,init
created_at: "2026-06-17T22:02:31.964Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-17T23:12:42.379Z"
author: codex-audit-20260618
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Fixed init positional target handling and existing-settings force guard for GH #262.
expected_result: Path-like pm init positional targets create/initialize the target tracker and do not rewrite the caller tracker unless --force is explicitly used for existing settings.
actual_result: "Path-like targets are detected, existing settings rewrites require --force, help text documents prefix-or-path, focused tests/manual temp-project reproduction/full coverage/dogfood passed."
